                  </hi>. I am a medical student. On 30th Dec. I was passing through Long-lane, Smithfield, about 8 o'clock in the evening—I felt something behind me, looked round, and saw the prisoner with my hand<lb></lb>kerchief in his hand—he threw it into the street, and ran away—a friend who was with me followed him, and caught him—I gave the handkerchief to the officer.</p>
               <p>
